timing_write_s...kslash_control(25.10)  timing_write_s...kslash_control(25.10)

Name
       timing_write_sdf_no_escape_backslash_control

Syntax
       timing_write_ sdf_no_escape_backslash_control

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Controls  how  the write_sdf command handles escape characters when the
       -no_escape parameter is specified.

       For example, consider the following input Verilog expression:

               \a/b\/c\/d

       When the global is set to true, the write_sdf command removes the first
       escape character and outputs a/b\/c\/d in the SDF file.

       When set to false, the command removes all the  escape  characters  and
       outputs a/b/c/d.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

